<p>Lastly, you can facilitate the deposit of funds from exchanges into your users&#8217; BNB Wallets, allowing them to easily move their funds between platforms.</p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Authentication and Authorization in Wallet APIs</h3>



<p>Implementing BNB Wallet APIs into your application requires authenticating and authorizing wallet APIs. Authentication ensures that only authorized users can access the wallet APIs, while authorization determines the level of access and actions they can perform. To understand this concept better, let&#8217;s explore a table that compares authentication and authorization in wallet APIs:</p>



<figure class="wp-block-table"><table><thead><tr><th>Authentication</th><th>Authorization</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Verifies user&#8217;s identity</td><td>Determines user&#8217;s privileges</td></tr><tr><td>Validates credentials</td><td>Controls access to specific resources</td></tr><tr><td>Protects against unauthorized access</td><td>Manages user roles and permissions</td></tr><tr><td>Examples: API keys, OAuth tokens</td><td>Examples: Read-only access, transfer tokens</td></tr></tbody></table></figure>



